[1] Case updates
- Thu 10 Jan 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=e3acf00149

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 9 Jan 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 630, of which 582 are confirmed and 48 are probable. In total, there were 385 deaths (337 confirmed and 48 probable) and 226 people recovered.
- 122 suspect cases under investigation.
- 2 new deaths of confirmed cases, including 1 in Katwa and 1 in Biena. Both are community deaths.
- 4 new recoveries released from Butembo ETC.

News of the response
Vaccination
-----------
- Since the beginning of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018, 58 085 people have been vaccinated, including 19 783 in Beni [North Kivu], 11 793 in Katwa [North Kivu], 6746 in Butembo [North Kivu], 5611 in Mabalako [North Kivu], 2283 in Kalunguta [North Kivu], 1740 in Komanda [Ituri], 1663 in Mandima [Ituri], 1272 in Oicha [North Kivu], 1285 in Goma [North Kivu], 791 in Vuhovi [North Kivu], 750 in Masereka [North Kivu], 735 in Kyondo [North Kivu], 700 in Lubero [North Kivu], 599 in Mutwanga [North Kivu], 558 in Karisimbi [North Kivu], 434 in Bunia [Ituri], 394 in Musienene [North Kivu], 355 in Tchomia [Ituri], 167 in Nyankunde [North Kivu], 70 in Biena [North Kivu], 63 in Alimbongo [North Kivu], 54 in Nyiragongo [North Kivu], and 13 in Kisangani [Tshopo].

- The only vaccine to be used in this outbreak is the rVSV-ZEBOV vaccine, manufactured by the pharmaceutical group Merck, following approval by the Ethics Committee in its decision of 19 May 2018.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteurs Mary Marshall and Kunihiko Iizuka

- Wed 9 Jan 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=83a6fcb988

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 8 Jan 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 628, of which 580 are confirmed and 48 are probable. In total, there were 383 deaths (335 confirmed and 48 probable) and 222 people recovered.
- Data unavailable for suspected cases under investigation today.
- 1 new confirmed case in Katwa.
- 1 new death of a confirmed cases in Katwa (community death).
- 1 new recovery released from Butembo ETC.

News of the response
1st birth at ETC
------------------
- [A girl] is the 1st baby born to a patient who has been cured of Ebola. She was born on Sun 6 Jan 2019 at the Ebola treatment center in Beni. She weighs 3.7 kg [8.2 lb], she is in good health and she is not contaminated by Ebola. Her mother, who was pregnant at the time, was infected with the virus and admitted to the ETC in December 2018. When she was cured, she was discharged from the ETC but she continued to be monitored to monitor the baby's development. Given the risk that the baby was also contaminated, the mother agreed to give birth in the ETC. Fortunately, the baby has been tested twice and the results have come back negative.

Vaccination
-----------
Since vaccination began on 8 Aug 2018, 57 471 people have been vaccinated [total numbers of people vaccinated in North Kivu, Ituri, and Tshopo provinces as of 9 Jan 2019 can be seen in the report above].

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[Always a happy occasion when a baby is born healthy, but this is an especially exciting event since the baby was born to an Ebola-infected mother who was cured of infection, and the baby is Ebola-free! This little girl is the 1st baby born to a patient who has been cured of Ebola. A glimmer of hope in the midst of so much trouble. - Mod.LK]

